A Polistes dominula is a species of paper wasp belonging to the family Vespidae.
They are typically black in color with bright yellow bands on their abdomen.
Their body is elongated and slender, with a narrow waist and characteristic long wings.
The texture of their body is smooth and shiny, with fine hairs covering their legs and antennae.
Polistes dominula can often be found building their papery nests on eaves, windowsills, and other structures.
They are commonly found throughout Europe, Asia, and North Africa.
Their sting can be painful, but they are generally not aggressive unless provoked.
